# Migrate Scoutriq Vision to TensorRT (.engine) on RunPod

Deploy Scoutriq Vision to a RunPod cloud instance using TensorRT (`.engine`) models to achieve maximum inference performance. Since TensorRT engines are highly specific to the GPU architecture and TensorRT version, models must be exported directly on the target RunPod hardware.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `.engine` files in your local `weights/` directory (e.g. `best2.engine`) will likely crash on RunPod with a TensorRT architecture mismatch error unless the RunPod instance has the exact same GPU as your local machine.

## User Review Required

- Please review the steps below. The primary change is that we will use `.pt` files to generate new `.engine` files *on the RunPod instance itself*, rather than uploading the local `.engine` files.

